				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">VMAIN has three increment modes: one adding 1 for horizontal transfers, one adding 32 for columns of mode 0-6 nametables, and one adding 128 for columns of mode 7 nametables. Writing to VRAM uses whatever increment mode is set in VMAIN, regardless of whether it's through PIO or DMA.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

